Dear Millwood Families,
The State Board of Education is mandating all districts to close down campuses and provide a distant learning option. In order to meet this educational requirement, Millwood Public Schools needs to understand what type of access your child has to technology and the internet. The information obtained will help us provide meaningful and productive online educational experience or if we need to provide another option for your family. This survey will also inform us if any household is in need of obtaining the learning tools necessary, such as the internet or devices. Please take a few moments and fill out the online survey. https://forms.gle/oa1XmijMoLPAsu5d6

post_text: This weekend, the Millwood administration has been monitoring the forecast through the National Weather Service and various local news outlets. Currently, the outlook is for severe weather to approach central Oklahoma by noon Monday, with an increasing possibility for dangerous conditions throughout the afternoon, evening, and overnight into Tuesday morning.Out of an abundance of caution, we have made the decision to cancel classes for Monday, May 20, 2019. All school-sponsored activities are also cancelled.Students will not have to make up the school day scheduled for tomorrow.We thank you for your understanding and apologize for any inconvenience.
